docs.lead_paragraph: Scientists trying to predict the consequences of climate change see few havens from future storms, floods and droughts. But some regions will fare much better than others.
docs.abstract: Scientists trying to predict consequences of climate change in United States say all areas of country will be affected, but some regions will fare better than others; although few people today are moving long distances to strategize for climate change, some Americans are at least pondering the question of where they would go based on impact of weather on comfort, safety and cost of living.

headline.seo: On a Warmer Planet, Which Cities Will Be Safest?
headline.main: Portland Will Still Be Cool, but Anchorage May Be the Place to Be

docs.snippet: India’s new prime minister, Narendra Modi, offers himself as a metaphor for the India he wants to build — ambitious, confident and impatient with slackness of any kind.
docs.lead_paragraph: India’s new prime minister, Narendra Modi, offers himself as a metaphor for the India he wants to build — ambitious, confident and impatient with slackness of any kind.
docs.abstract: Indian Prime Min Narendra Modi comes to New York for five days as an immensely popular leader and a sought-after strategic partner; it is big moment for him, as he offers himself as a metaphor for the India he wants to build--ambitious, confident and impatient with slackness of any kind; he is building a machine for governing in India, one he intends to operate for a long time.
